headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Expedia Group (EXPE) After Its 57% One-Year Rally?
summary: If you are wondering whether Expedia Group’s share price still reflects good value after a strong run, you are not alone. This article is built to help you frame that question clearly. The stock last closed at US$290.76, with returns of 2.6% over 30 days and 57.1% over the past year. These returns can shift how the market views both its growth potential and its risk. headline: Expedia Group to Webcast Fourth Quarter 2025 Results on February 12, 2026
summary: SEATTLE, January 15, 2026--Expedia Group (NASDAQ: EXPE) will report its fourth quarter 2025 results for the period ended December 31, 2025, on Thursday, February 12, 2026 via an earnings release and accompanying webcast. These items will be available in the Investor Relations section of the company’s corporate website at http://ir.expediagroup.com.
